A '''Rich Assessment Task''' or R.A.T is a closed set of questions that allows for some imagination or communication of ideas by [[student]]s. They are commonly used in [[math]] by teachers who have a deep understanding of their students. They provide no use in rating students according to the VELS Ratings System.

